peopleAlsoAsk.question: How can I tell how old my Royal Typewriter is?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: Take your serial number (on the top of the frame under the right end of the carriage) here, https://typewriterdatabase.com/royal.72.typewriter-serial-number-database , and look for your number within one of the ranges given to find the year.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: Are antique typewriters worth anything?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: ‍Yes, old typewriters can be valuable collectibles, with some models selling for hundreds or even thousands of dollars. The value depends on the brand, age, condition, rarity, and market demand. If you own a vintage typewriter, researching its model and history can help determine its worth.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: How old does a typewriter have to be to be considered antique?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: An antique, by definition in the U.S., is any object that is 100 years old and older. Items not yet 100 years old are considered vintage.

peopleAlsoAsk.question: What year did Royal Typewriter come out?
peopleAlsoAsk.snippet: In March 1906 the first Royal typewriter, the Royal Standard, was sold. The Royal Standard was set apart from its competition by its 'flatbed' design.
